                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>Nothing apart from virtue must be reckoned as the only good [Loeb 40, 227].</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="English_secretary">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        inauditum rei nomen
                        imponere.
                        factis no[m]i[ni]b[us] et novis vti. 
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>
                The name of the matter is novel.
                To impose
                To use new words coined for an occasion.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="English_secretary" anchor_text="vocabulis vterentur nobis incognitis, vsitatis sibi; nominibus notauit nouis; non tam rerum inuentor fuit, 
            qu&agrave;m nouoru[m] verborum; non peruagatis, inusitatis verbis vterentur">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        verba parie[n]da
                        impone[n]da nova novis rebus no[m]i[n]a
                        multa novitas nominu[m].
                        more quoda[m] loquu[n]tur suo
                        verbis in dice[n]do quasi priuatis vtuntur ac suis
                        vocabulis vtuntur nobis incogintis vsitatis sibi.
                        nominibus notauit novis.
                        no[n] ta[m] reru[m] inve[n]tor q[uam] novor[um] [deleted] verbor[um].
                        invsitatis verbis vti
                        verbis no[n] p[er]vagatis vti.
                        nova rebus imponere no[m]i[n]a.
                        no[m]i[n]a novari
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>
                Terms must be made up.
                New words must be established for new things.
                A great novelty of names.
                They speak in their own certain way.
                They use words in speaking as if personal and their own.  
                They use vocabularies unknown to us, but known to themselves.
                It denoted with new names.
                Not so much an inventor of things as of new words.
                To use unknown words.
                To use words not widely known.
                To assign new names to things.
                To change names.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="English_secretary" anchor_text="infici debet his artibus, quas si du[m] est tener co[m]biberit">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        infici artibus
                        co[m]bibere artes.
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>
                To be dyed by the arts.
                To soak in the arts.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="English_secretary" anchor_text="in re">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>in re</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>In essence.</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
